== Theme ==
Vulcore is a volcanic wasteland environment defined by:
* Lava flows, sulphur pits, and unstable ground
* Ancient Scaven tribal territories and burial mounds
* Renegade military installations and blast walls
* Mysterious encounters with supernatural factions (the [[Fallen]] and the [[Angels]])
* Powerful energy storms that can strip cash multipliers and drain energy
* Hidden firewells, canyons, caves, and plateaus scattered across the plain

The atmosphere is hostile and unpredictable. Controllers must balance aggression with caution — venturing too deep into sulphur fields attracts [[Enforcers]], while reckless exploration can trigger ambushes or waste precious [[KCharge]].

== Sub-Zones ==

=== Vulcore Plain (Main Area) ===
The open patrol area of Vulcore. Contains the majority of standard enemy encounters, [[Mercenary Outpost|Mercenary Outposts]], [[Tag Droid|Tag Droids]], [[Renegade]] squads, [[Scaven]] patrols, and random events. The main area connects to all other sub-zones.

* '''Mercenary Outposts''' — Found scattered across the plain. Offer services: hire mercs, earn mercreds (missions), repairs, and items for sale. Available missions from outposts include: Banking, Cave Crystals, Matriarch Crowns, and Sulphur Anomaly.
* '''Caves''' — Can be entered with or without an [[Orbiter]]. Sending in an Orbiter first is safer. Caves may contain enemies, equipment, or be empty.
* '''Canyons''' — Hidden canyons can be blasted open or entered directly. Some are hidden and require discovery. Note: the [[Fallen]] curse does ''not'' apply inside canyons.
* '''Destroyed Outposts''' — Ruined outposts that can be investigated for loot or enemies.
* '''Renegade Bases''' — Fortified installations defended by [[Renegade]] squads and blast walls. Contain a [[Renegade Base Commander]] (RBC). Defeating the RBC yields significant rewards including [[Magma Technology]] and [[Bulwark Technology]] segments.
* '''Renegade Uplink Bases''' — A variant of Renegade Bases with an [[Uplink Controller]] unit.
* '''Renegade Workshops''' — Can be attacked directly or by luring sentries out first.
* '''Farms''' — Scaven worker farms. Can demand tribute, attack workers (gains negative alignment), or leave.
* '''Distress Calls''' — Trapped squads that can be freed (gains positive alignment) or destroyed.
* '''[[Tag Droid|Tag Droids]]''' — Fast [[Orbiter]]-chassis enemies carrying a [[Credit Bank]] module. Intercepting and defeating them yields bonus credits. A primary source of cash on patrol.
* '''Consoles''' — Can be opened for rewards, but opening them can replace an active cash multiplier (Greed/Enrichment) with a standard 10x multiplier — avoid if you have Greed/Enrichment active.

=== Scaven Territory ===
A distinct sub-zone entered from the main Vulcore plain via Scaven Totems. Scaven Territory is the homeland of the [[Scaven]] faction and contains a dense concentration of Scaven units, settlements, burial mounds, and fortifications.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Scaven Settlements''' — Friendly Scaven villages that can be contacted. Offer two mission types:
** '''Raze an Outpost''' — Costs mercreds; easier if you have drain.
** '''Kill bots at a Burial Mound''' — Becomes very difficult at high BM.
** Upon completion, the Scaven may repair one bot (Ion Bath) and offer: Scaven Mercs, XP multiplier, Coordinates, or buy positive alignment (very expensive).
* '''Scaven Burial Mounds''' — Can be investigated. May contain Crowns or Construction Notes (CN), but looting them grants negative alignment.
* '''Scaven Forts''' — Fortified Scaven positions. Attacking them risks encountering [[Malevolent Matriarch|Malevolent Matriarchs]] at higher BM.
* '''[[Scaven Ziggurat]]''' — A massive ancient structure. Requires all four [[Runes]] equipped on squad bots to open. Rewards the unique [[SxD8]] shield (once per reset).
* '''Sun Ritual''' — A special event in Scaven Territory (also found on the plain). Scaven Matriarchs perform a ritual around a glowing rune stone. Defeating them yields the [[Sun Rune]] and 4 Crowns. Best attempted at low BM to face only 1 Matriarch.
* '''Ice Queen''' — A special Matriarch variant found in Scaven Settlements highlighted in blue by an [[Anomaly Detector]]. Defeating her yields the [[Ice Rune]] and 1 Crown. Has 200 armour. Can only be fought once.
* '''Scaven Mercs''' — Hired by completing a Scaven mission. Follow the squad everywhere in Vulcore but prevent entry to Mercenary Outposts (must be dropped first). Can be taken out of Scaven Territory, making the squad very powerful in normal Vulcore. Attacking multiple settlements turns them hostile until you return to your workshop.

