=== Lava Fields ===
A dangerous sub-zone accessible from the main Vulcore plain. The Lava Fields are the location of [[Azra's Arena]] and [[Fallen]] encounters.

'''Key features:'''
* '''[[Azra's Arena]]''' — A tournament found within the Lava Fields. Offers two options:
** '''To the Tournament''' — 6 rounds of increasingly difficult combat. Winning yields cash prizes scaled to the player's squad BM. Only one Azra tournament per Lava Field visit — leave immediately after winning if farming cash.
** '''[[Master Controllers]]''' — A special high-difficulty battle against the Master Controllers squad. Defeating them rewards a unique CyBot ([[CySeer]] or [[CySentinel]]). Requires significant preparation (see [[Master Controllers]] section).
* '''[[Fallen]] Encounter''' — A random encounter in the Lava Fields (requires negative alignment). The Fallen offer:
** '''[[Greed]]''' — 10x cash multiplier. Costs 20 Mercreds and alignment. Equivalent to Enrichment for negative-align players.
** '''Coords - Azra''' — Coordinates to Azra's Arena (bypasses searching).
** '''Imps''' — 3 [[Orbiter]]-chassis bots with 3x [[TC7 Target Predictor]] and [[Baron Battery]] each. Fast, high critical hit chance, but defensively weak.
** '''Dark Union''' — 2 Demon ([[Bulwark]]), 2 Fiend ([[Overseer]]), and either 1 Baal or 1 Beelzebub ([[Leviathan]]) join the squad. Grants +180% fire rate, 12% critical hit chance, and ~1000 projected shield. Comes with a curse: every step without fighting or finding something drains cash and XP, growing with each step.
* '''Lava Damage''' — Moving through certain areas of the Lava Fields can cause damage to the squad.
* '''Firewells''' — Found in the Lava Fields (and occasionally elsewhere). Can be activated for rewards including database access, AI boosts, and rune discovery. Activating an unstable Firewell is risky. Requires an [[Orbiter]] to safely use the access shaft. The [[Fire Rune]] can be found in Firewells (and Magma Labs).

=== Plateau ===
An elevated sub-zone accessible from the main Vulcore plain. The Plateau contains unique encounters not found elsewhere.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Sink Holes''' — Discovered by an [[Anomaly Detector]]. Some are booby-trapped and require an [[Orbiter]] to defuse. The [[Moon Rune]] (Lunar Rune) is found only in Sink Holes discovered by an Anomaly Detector that have been booby-trapped.
* '''Phoenix Fortress''' — A fortified position on the Plateau. Can be explored or attacked.
* '''Consoles''' — Present on the Plateau. Opening them can replace Greed/Enrichment with a standard 10x multiplier — avoid if you have an active multiplier.
* '''Tag Droids''' — Found on the Plateau, making it a good farming spot for credits when on a Greed/Enrichment run (after 400 KC on Greed, per experienced players).
* '''Ground Unstable''' — Moving through certain areas may trigger ground instability events.

'''Note:''' Avoid the Plateau if you have Greed/Enrichment active and do not want to risk losing it to a console or cash multiplier event.

=== Sulphur Fields (Sulphur Pits) ===
A high-danger sub-zone that becomes accessible after defeating the [[Master Controllers]] and obtaining a CyBot. The Sulphur Fields are the primary location for farming [[Technology]] segments and high-level XP.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Magma Squads''' — Magma-type enemies (Flamers, Ash, Blazers, Fire Streakers, Combustus, Inferno, Fire Crawlers, Fire Lords, etc.) that drop [[Magma Technology]] segments.
* '''Annihilators''' — Powerful boss-tier enemies that appear in the Sulphur Fields. Described as "mini Termies" — easier than a Terminus but still very dangerous as they bring Seers. Upon defeat, drop a superweapon based on BM: [[Thermal Dawn]] (low BM), [[Riot Gun]] (mid BM), or [[Obliterator]] (high BM).
* '''Enforcers''' — Appear if the squad stays in the Sulphur Fields too long. Grow progressively stronger with each encounter. Most players return to an outpost to drop mercreds and re-enter for a fresh run rather than fighting Enforcers repeatedly.
* '''Sulphur Workshops''' — Found in the Sulphur Fields. Contain [[Magma Technology]], [[Bulwark Technology]], and [[Crusader Technology]] segments.
* '''Crusader Technology''' — Primarily obtained in the Sulphur Fields. The [[Crusader]] chassis is the main reward of Sulphur Field runs.
* '''Magma Lords''' — Powerful Leviathan-chassis enemies (Lord Magmas) armed with 8x Morning Star weapons and EM Repulsor Field modules. Drop [[Magma Technology]] and [[Bulwark Technology]] segments.

