==== Scaven Mercs ====
Obtained by completing a mission for a friendly [[Scaven Settlement]] in [[Scaven Territory]]. Not hired with Mercreds — earned through gameplay.

The composition and quality of Scaven Mercs scales with the player's squad BM. Higher BM squads receive more powerful Scaven units, including higher-grade Shielder variants and the Scaven Hero.

<gallery widths="120" heights="100">
File:Scavenboss.jpg|[[Scaven Boss]]
File:Scavenshielders.jpg|[[Scaven Shielders]]
</gallery>

* '''[[Scaven Boss]]''' — Scaven Commander chassis; [[Pistol]] weapon; [[Inspiration]] module. Provides squad-wide buffs to speed, fire rate, and accuracy.
* '''[[Scaven Warlord]]''' — Scaven Commander chassis; [[Pistol]] weapon; Leadership module.
* '''[[Scaven Hero]]''' — A higher-grade Scaven Commander unit available at higher squad BM. Provides enhanced squad buffs.
* '''[[Scaven Shielders]]''' (basic) — Scaven Shielders chassis; [[Baron (Shield)|Baron]] x2 shields; [[Pistol]] x2. Low-BM variant.
* '''[[Scaven Heavy Shield]]''' — Scaven Shielders chassis; [[Photonic SV]] x2 shields; [[Sub-Machine Gun]] x2. Mid-BM variant.
* '''[[Scaven Shield Matrix]]''' — Scaven Shielders chassis; [[Argon (Shield)|Argon]] x2 shields; [[Assault Rifle]] x2. High-BM variant.
* '''[[Scaven Assault Squad]]''' — Scaven Strike Gang chassis; Rocket Launcher x3, [[Assault Rifle]] x3.
* Various Scaven warrior units accompany the squad.

Scaven Mercs prevent entry to Mercenary Outposts while active. Must be dropped before entering an outpost.

