== Farming: Credits ==
The best sources of credits in Vulcore:

* '''[[Tag Droid|Tag Droids]]''' — [[Orbiter]]-chassis enemies with a [[Credit Bank]] module. Fast and found across the plain and Plateau. Primary credit source on patrol. Intercepting them is the main goal of Banking missions.
* '''[[Azra's Arena]]''' — Each tournament win yields cash scaled to the player's squad BM. Only 1 Azra per Lava Field — leave immediately after winning to find another field.
* '''[[Greed]] / [[Enrichment]]''' — 10x cash multiplier from [[Fallen]] (negative align) or [[Angels]] (positive align). The single most important cash multiplier in the game. Avoid consoles, Plateau, and anything that might replace it with a standard 10x multiplier.
* '''EX Bots''' — Special rare enemy bots ([[EX20]], [[EX21]], [[EX22]], [[EX23]], [[EX24]]) that appear as random encounters. High credit yield per fight.

'''Tips:'''
* Use a [[Bounty Enhancer]] module (available on the [[Pulse]] merc or purchasable) to increase credit drops.
* The Fallen's [[Greed]] gift costs 20 Mercreds + alignment but pays for itself quickly.
* Avoid opening Consoles while Greed/Enrichment is active.

== Farming: Experience (XP) ==
The best sources of XP in Vulcore:

* '''[[Sulphur Fields]]''' — The primary XP farming zone in Vulcore. Magma enemies, Crusader-type enemies, and Annihilators all yield high XP. Run Sulphur Fields until Enforcers appear, then return to outpost and re-enter.
* '''[[Scaven Territory]]''' — Levelling bots in Scaven Territory is a common early-game strategy. Scaven enemies are numerous and provide steady XP. Recommended to level Reapers to AI 6–9 here before major patrol runs.
* '''XP Multipliers''' — Available at outposts or from Scaven Settlements. Stack with combat XP.

'''Note:''' XP is shared among all bots in the squad. Fewer bots = more XP per bot. Levelling bots individually (e.g., sending a single bot to the CCU Training Deck) is faster for early levels.

== Notable Events & Encounters ==

=== Distress Calls ===
Trapped squads found on patrol. Freeing them grants positive alignment. Destroying them grants negative alignment and some credits.

=== Scaven Proposal ===
After completing a Scaven mission, the Scaven offer a choice of rewards. Options include Scaven Mercs, XP multiplier, Coordinates, or buying positive alignment (very expensive at 250,000 cash per point).

=== Phoenix Fortress ===
A fortified position on the Plateau. Can be explored or attacked for rewards.

=== Renegade Power Plant ===
A Renegade installation that can be investigated for rewards.

=== EX Bots ===
Special enemy bots ([[EX20]], [[EX21]], [[EX22]], [[EX23]], [[EX24]]) that appear as rare encounters. High-value targets with significant credit and XP rewards.

=== Sealed Tombs and Vaults ===
* '''Sealed Tomb''' — Can be blown open. May contain equipment or enemies.
* '''Sealed Vault''' — Can be opened. May contain Technology segments, equipment, or be empty.

=== Magma Technology Lab ===
A special location that can be investigated for Magma Technology information and segments.

